Sentencas: Three solid oxide fuel cells were tested at high current densities to determine interfacial effects.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The cathodes used were fired at different temperatures to study the dependence on the strontium content at the interface.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: Microanalysis of three green cells were used to compare the results.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The results indicate that strontium is present at the GDC/YSZ interface in all cells green or tested.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The untested cells indicate that the strontium content increases with increasing cathode firing temperature.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The tested cells, however, show a reverse trend.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: While strontium continues to move to the interface, the strontium content increases with decreasing cathode firing temperature.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: Cathodes were fired at 1025, 1050, and 1075 degrees C, and the percent change in power densities after testing were - 10.7, - 27.0, and + 5.0%, respectively.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The cell whose cathode was fired at 1075 degrees C showed a positive improvement over time.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities

Sentencas: The cell whose cathode was fired at 1025 degrees C delaminated during dis-assembly indicating poor adhesion with the GDC layer.
Titulo: Interfacial long-term effects of LSCF cathodes fired at different temperatures and tested at high current densities
